      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "When everything feels meaningless, it's a profound sign of how deeply you are hurting. The world can feel hollow when the person who gave it shape is gone, and that feeling of pointlessness is a natural, though agonizing, response to such a massive loss. If the weight of that emptiness becomes too much to bear, please consider reaching out to someone who can help you carry this burden. There are people who want to support you through this darkness.",
      "source": "target",
